# Project Context

Short, strict, factual. Not a PRD.

## Project Name

oc-visual-test-runner

## Current Stage

Phase 0 — scaffold conversion (documentation and context only; no runtime).

## Project Purpose

Persona-based visual UX testing runner. VLM observes screen → structured action → platform adapter executes → feedback observation → trace/result output until `done`, `blocked`, `max_steps`, or `timeout`.

## Phase 1 Supported Targets

- `figma` — Figma prototype URL in browser
- `web` — website URL in browser
- Both use a **shared browser adapter**

## Planned Future Targets

- `android` — future platform adapter (not implemented)
- `windows` — future platform adapter (not implemented)

## Core Architecture Direction

```text
target config → platform adapter → observation frame
  → VLM action decision → action execution → feedback observation → trace/result output
```

Organized around a **universal visual agent loop**.

## Current Non-Goals

- No runtime code, Gemini, Playwright, or browser adapter implementation
- No Android or Windows adapters
- No OpenClaw deployment integration
- No Figma API grounding or DOM-selector-first automation
- No legacy runner migration

## Cursor Agent Must Not Assume

- Runtime or CLI (`scripts/ux_testing.py`) already exists — check `docs/TASKS.md`
- Failed clicks automatically mean UX issues
- Legacy `figma_runner.py` / `web_runner.py` exist in this repo
- Package layout or `requirements.txt` is finalized — decide in Phase 1
- Real API keys belong in the repo — use `.env` locally only
